Always wanted to visit - little taken back
May 2019 ‚Ä¢ Solo
To start off you need to know I live in New Zealand...land of clean green rivers and lakes.
So I spent two nights in ha long bay to get to really see the area and the sites , this first thing to note is it is really touristy, a bit
Ike Niagara Falls, a natural wonder surrounded by high rises etc..., ha long is boarded by alot of shipping docks and massive city construction all pushed to tourism. You don't actually travel far into the bay . And all the other boats are there with you each day. The big problem is pollution...it is really bad , oil slicks , floating debris in the water and not a clean beach anywhere.
So again I am from nz so this took me back and I was disappointed, but talking to others that come from different parts , they loved the area.
So different strokes for different folks
