2.0 of 5 bubbles
Not worth it!
May 2019 ‚Ä¢ Couples
I have been to Langkawi, Fiji, Palawan and Krabi so I have seen plenty of beautiful limestone cliffs and paradise landscapes.
All of them are nicer than Halong Bay.
Sorry to say, but Halong Bay just isn't worth it. The water is dirty, rubbish floats around the sea, the jetty feels like an airport such is the volume of tourists piling onto the hundreds of boats that overcrowd the bay.
Basically, Vietnam has killed the goose that laid the golden egg by mismanaging what should be a world class attraction. For anyone going to Thailand or Phillippines after Vietnam, I suggest giving Halong Bay a miss. The bay is overrated, expensive to visit, and by not going you will be doing our planet a favor.
Written May 9, 2019
Ron Douglas
