Ha Long Bay
Apr 2019 ‚Ä¢ Solo
I can not agree more to my previous travel expert. It is a bloody noisy and dusty place. I did plan, pay and book everything ahaed, but not the sailing boat and the harbour cruise. Weather was moderate to poor in 2 1/2 days, so I was "only" stuck but deeply disappointed as there is really nothing else one can do. The main road will look soon like Las Vegas. About 80 new developments coming up in yellow, white, pink and green. Artdeco style but so does not fit in the landscape. And yes, there is plenty of loud and inexperienced Chinese travellers in the area. Patience and quietness is not their biggest strength.
Esphe
20 contributions
Polluted, overcrowded, disastrous!
This was probably the lowest point of our Vietnam trip. We went on a 1day trip from Hanoi. The trip started of bad since the bus was really small and uncomfortable and the toilet stop was waaaaay too long (same for the way back).
We thought we were ready for the massive crowds of tourists, but this was on a next level. Hundreds, if not thousands of people go to the same three spots in the same order, like there is no common sense. The boats crash with each other to get the tourist out and on the boat which can be quite dangerous.

I could bear all of that, but when i saw the polluted water, this is what hurt me the most. It‚Äôs terrible what they have done with this place. I believe it used to be nice but there is basically nothing to enjoy there. When we went on the kayak and we were close to the water we could actually smell the terrible smell that came from the water. I would not swim in there if my life depended on it.
So do yourself a favor and skip it since it‚Äôs only gonna get worse unless the government will shut it down and let it recover.
