Unique Journey to Ha Long Bay
Jan 2019 ‚Ä¢ Family
Serenity Cruises is very good choice to explore Ha Long Bay. Instead of touristy area (Like Sung Sot Cave or Luon Cave) they keep cruising much further to very quite view where 40 km far away. Anchor in Lan Ha Bay for a nite is perfect moment and visiting Viet Hai village the next day.
If you are looking for a quite route and a real Ha Long - Lan Ha - Cat Ba island, Ha Long Serenity Cruises recommended.
Written January 17, 2019
Antonia A
Squamish, Canada4 contributions
THE WORST TOUR COMPANY I HAVE EVER DEALT WITH
Sep 2018 ‚Ä¢ Solo
This was by far the worst tour experience of my life. The tour was full of what was a decidedly mediocre tour full of blunders and poor customer service. The first issue was that the air conditioning in the rooms wasn't turned on until after 8:30pm despite it being over 33 degrees celsius out plus humidity. The second was that the food was plainly terrible. After having the most amazing food everywhere I'd been in Vietnam, this mash of westernized combination of chinese and japanese food was really disappointing. All the food was clearly microwaved and it tasted awful. The beds on the boats were like sleeping on bare box springs, you could feel the springs poking through the bed. Crazy uncomfortable beds even for Vietnam where most beds are hard as rock. The boat staff were quite rude and although we had purchased many drinks from their bar, they demanded that we drink the one bottle of wine we brought with us in our room (the un-airconditioned one that was like a sauna) or pay them a service charge. The cruise was cut short due to an incoming storm which wasn't their fault obviously, but rather than just refund the guests the difference for missing some of the meals and activities, they insisted on taking us kayaking at 6am and missing lunch.
All of that could have been chalked up to just bad luck on my part, but the worst part of the whole experience is that on top of all of that they gave me back another passenger's passport, rather than my own! I realized it when I was about to leave for the airport and missed my flight. Thankfully, I had made friends with the other passenger and though she was all the way in Danang, was able to get a hold of her. The tour company did handle getting the passports couriered back to us, but I had to change my flight and stay another night in a hotel which they promised to pay for. All in all this massive blunder cost me over $300 usd. The tour company has done absolutely nothing to compensate me in fact they have ignored or not replied to all of the messages I've sent requesting that this be dealt with.
I HIGHLY recommend avoiding APT tours at all costs. They not only offer a very low quality cruise experience, they are not careful with customer's belongings and do absolutely nothing to resolve a situation when they do screw up. I am utterly dismayed with the way this mess was handled.
Written September 25, 2018
